10:
I mean... Doesn't it feel a little
unnecessary at this point?
18: Are you really okay with that?
21:
If you do not apologize, surely your
feelings of inferiority will only grow
stronger, no?
25:
Could you maybe phrase that
better?!
30:
Huh, never seen you three hanging
out together.
35:
Ah, Nimbus, perfect timing! Maybe
you can talk some sense into him.
38: Sho still hasn't apologized to Yumu!
45:
It's not like he HAS to apologize, but
he's clearly worried about it.
49:
He keeps whining to me and Yuki
about what he should do, but then
he doesn't follow through...
54:
Now hold on a moment. Let's think
about this rationally.
57:
Should he really be forgiven? Surely
it's considered problematic to
physically harm your friend over a
simple misunderstanding...
67:
That's true, but... that wasn't exactly
under normal circumstances, so
maybe we should be a bit morâ€”
72:
What's the big deal? Alk's a softie.
I'm sure he's already forgiven a
numbskull like you.
78:
Okay, I get it! I just gotta go talk to
him, right?!
82:
I don't know about apologizing, but...
I can at least say what I wanna say
and get this load off my shoulders.
87: Yeah, yeah, do whatever you like.
92:
You know, the look in your eyes has
changed. Maybe I was wrong about
you.
97:
My eyes? Well, yeah, they're a
different color now...
101: So when are you going to talk to Alk?
110:
Cocoa powder, cocoa powder... Ah,
looks like I need to buy some more
soon...
115: Ow! Ow! Okay, okay! Quit pushing!
124:
Sho said he's got something he
wants to tell you! Anyway, I'm
leaving now, byeee!
134:
Uh, well... I mean, I don't want to
bring up the past, but...
143: I get it. We don't have to talk about it.
146:
Anyway, I was about to make some
hot cocoa. Want some?
154: I've always hated this side of yoâ€”
157:
Wait, no... That's not what I came
here to say.
163:
Back in middle school, I thought we
were close. Like, I looked out for you,
and you did the same for me.
165:
But you didn't seem to feel the same
way. I figured you were gonna leave
me behind, and I got scared...
173:
But, look, I'm not gonna be that
person anymore! I don't want any
more of your pity!
178:
So... you don't need to forgive me, or
whatever...
186:
I've wanted to say this for a while
now, but could you stop assuming
how I feel?
194:
Sure, I might've felt a little frustrated
with you... To be honest, you got on
my nerves a lot.
198:
And I can't tell you how often I'd wish
you could read the room!
206:
BUT! I never EVER did anything for
you out of pity! YOU'RE the one who
thought that!
210:
Sure, you can't read a room to save
your life, but that's not always a bad
thing! That's how we met, remember?
214:
You talked to me when no one else
would! So even if you can be a
frustrating idiot, I would never think
so lowly of you!
222:
Y-you've got a nasty way of
reassuring people, you know that?
Maybe YOU can't read a room!
227:
Yeah, right! Remember what you
said to Serizawa when we were
first-years?!
231:
Huh? But EVERYBODY knew she was
into you!
235:
You don't say that TO HER FACE!
That's what I'm talking about!
239:
Well, how was I supposed to know
that?!
243:
Hello, Nao. How is Sho's apology
going?
247:
Oh, I'd say pretty good. They're
fighting like friends again.
253:
Don't get all high and mighty on me
just 'cause you're popular with the
ladies!
257: What are you talking about NOW?!
261:
It sounds like they're having fun. Do
you think they'd let me join?
265:
I don't think they'd be a very good
influence on you...
269:
Don't play dumb with me! I heard
you're practically surrounded by
beautiful babes day and night!
272:
They're making fun of me! They're
not ACTUALLY flirting with me!
275:
That's not true for all of them, and
you know it!
278:
W-well, I made sure to reject those
that did feel that way!
282: You did WHAT?! Are you an idiot?!
291:
*sigh* From my point of view, they
both are...
